		<div class="really_simple_share_clearfix"></div><p>An immersive show in complete darkness, Pitch Black was held at La Cinémathèque Québecoise Saturday 15th February. The event gathered poets, slammers, musicians all giving each unique performance.</p>
<p>Pitch Black is presented within the context of <a href="http://frobruary.blogspot.ca/">Frobruary</a> and of Black history month &#8211; the annual remembrance of important people and events in the history of African diaspora. The event was a special moment to reflect on social issues, and give a voice to those from marginalized minority groups. </p>
<p>In a pitch black room, you cannot see anything, merely shadows or faint silhouettes. Your auditory sense takes completely over over all senses, letting you imagine or reflect more:</p>
<p><img src="http://farm8.staticflickr.com/7341/12571360013_40e5c640e0_b.jpg" alt="pitch black - frobruary - cinematheque" width="900" height="600"  class="mainimageflickr" /></p>
<p><span id="more-665"></span></p>
<p>The Pitch Black event was instigated by Xav Ier, a local Montreal artist, original founder of Frobruary and also community worker. Here, we can see Xav Ier (top, second from left) with the whole organization team:</p>
<p><img src="http://farm4.staticflickr.com/3752/12571196075_1184bdc02e_b.jpg" alt="pitch black - frobruary - cinematheque" width="900" height="600"  class="mainimageflickr" /></p>
<p>The public could see the artists lined up in front before the beginning of the show &#8211; we could see excitement, a contrast to the quietness and darkness in the upcoming hour:</p>
<p><img src="http://farm3.staticflickr.com/2822/12571200385_95b19c3e31_b.jpg" alt="pitch black - frobruary - cinematheque"  /></p>
<p>Xav Ier presented the show &#8211; explaining that once the show begins, you cannot go in and out, so as not disrupt the experience. One of the consequence is that you don&#8217;t hear anyone moving and you&#8217;re totally focused on the performance:</p>
<p><img src="http://farm6.staticflickr.com/5500/12571198705_2aa36925c1_b.jpg" alt="pitch black - frobruary - cinematheque"  /></p>
<p>Once the show begins, the lights switches off. You lose your marks. The only light that&#8217;s visible is the EXIT sign, at the top right:</p>
<p><img src="http://farm8.staticflickr.com/7333/12571334193_5ed01ecfa6_b.jpg" alt="pitch black - frobruary - cinematheque"  /></p>
<p>Artists are waiting in pitch black &#8211; here you can guess silhouettes of artists in front of the public: </p>
<p><img src="http://farm4.staticflickr.com/3792/12571322043_dfc0927a13_b.jpg" alt="pitch black - frobruary - cinematheque" width="900" height="600"  class="mainimageflickr" /></p>
<p>There were many artists invited, mostly vocal artists, such as Ivy Slam, Fabrice Koffy Poesic, Tamara Brown and many others. They all took the microphone one by one, half in French and half in English, speaking about history, discrimination, gender issues &#8212; certainly a beautiful evening full of poetic voices:</p>
<p><img src="http://farm8.staticflickr.com/7425/12571346793_7e681a9ee7_b.jpg" alt="pitch black - frobruary - cinematheque"  /></p>
<p>Sometimes, an artist chose to add a candle to &#8220;light&#8221; their performance. That&#8217;s one single candle, that even adds more to the mystery, letting you guess more than really &#8220;see&#8221; what&#8217;s in front:</p>
<p><img src="http://farm6.staticflickr.com/5502/12571330533_11a3a294b8_b.jpg" alt="pitch black - frobruary - cinematheque" width="900" height="600"  class="mainimageflickr" /></p>
<p>As the evening progresses, the eyes get used to the darkness &#8211; and you begin to guess movements, a glimpse of faces, but like in the beginning, your attention is completely on the words and the sounds:</p>
<p><img src="http://farm3.staticflickr.com/2829/12571671784_c0ca3e072f_b.jpg" alt="pitch black - frobruary - cinematheque" width="900" height="600"  class="mainimageflickr" /></p>
<p>Between performances, a cello complemented the performances, an instrument you can see in the right :</p>
<p><img src="http://farm4.staticflickr.com/3702/12571350163_6934e2ccaf_b.jpg" alt="pitch black - frobruary - cinematheque" width="900" height="600"  class="mainimageflickr" /></p>
<p>An artist&#8217;s face is lighted by his laptop &#8211; used for written notes for his performance. </p>
<p><img src="http://farm8.staticflickr.com/7354/12571690184_7b4742a255_b.jpg" alt="pitch black - frobruary - cinematheque" width="900" height="600"  class="mainimageflickr" /></p>
<p>Pitch Black is certainly a unique performance &#8211; it moves you, it makes you uncomfortable by removing one of our most used sense : your eyes, and invites to dedicate your attention to the words. Too often, shows are designed with the sole objective of entertaining, and give the &#8220;customer&#8221; the most bang for his bucks, with lasers, banners, spotlights and latest gadgets. What if you go down to basics and create this experience? </p>
<p><a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/heri_quebec/sets/72157641077873624">See more pictures on tje Flickr set</a><br />
<a href="http://heriphotography.com">Photos by HeriPhotography</a><br />
Follow <a href="https://www.facebook.com/FrobruaryInternational">Frobruary on Facebook</a></p>
